Martyn Uzzell, 51, was riding from Land's End to John O'Groats for Macmillan Cancer Support when he was thrown into path of a four-inch deep pothole .
Just a month before tragedy, council sent workers to inspect the hole after police said it was a hazard .
But it was decided that immediate repairs were not necessary .
A month before the tragedy, the council inspected the road twice but failed to take any action .
Coroner ruled that the state of the A65 near Giggleswick was 'the cause of the incident'